Mozambican President Filipe Nyusi told the U.S.-Africa Business Summit his country "is back on the path to economic growth and development", showing clear signs of overcoming the obstacles it has faced recently. The leader of the nation in southeastern Africa was the only head-of-state to address the gathering. While in Washington, DC, Nyusi held talks with American corporations to discuss business opportunities and was received by Secretary of State Rex Tillerson, The two met previously last September in New York, when Tillerson was still CEO of Exxon, which has been granted licenses to explore for natural gas in three offshore blocks.